sentences: Marian Grudeff (April 18, 1927 – November 4, 2006) was a Canadian concert pianist  music teacher and musical theatre composer of Bulgarian origin.
She performed extensively in Canada and the United States in the 1940s, and taught at the Royal Conservatory of Music from 1948 to 1952.
